CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper November 16, 1963, pg. 4, reads: "'Teenie Harris' Son Escapes Injury - Lionel Harris, son of Courier photographer Charles H. (Teenie) Harris, miraculously escaped serious injury, early last Saturday, on the Leechburg Road from New Kensington to Pittsburgh, when he fell asleep at the wheel of his father's car and the auto plunged down a 30-foot embankment (left photo, shown by arrows). The smashed car, almost a total wreck, is shown in the right photo. Young Harris suffered only two bumps on his head. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Leechburg Road at site of Lionel Harris's car accident in Teenie Harris's car, with Valley High School playing fields on right, New Kensington
